<section id="command-posxyz">
<title>POSXYZ</title>
<indexterm><primary>POSXYZ</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>POSXYZ</command></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Outputs the turtle's current position, as a list of three numbers, the X, Y, and Z coordinates.
</para>
<para>
POSXYZ is designed to run in <link linkend="command-perspective">PERSPECTIVE</link> mode.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
<programlisting><userinput>PERSPECTIVE
SETPOSXYZ [100 200 300]
SHOW POSXYZ</userinput>
[100 200 300]
</programlisting>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>
</section>
